2500|$|By Wedderburn's theorem, every finite {{division}} ring is commutative, {{and therefore a}} finite field. Another condition ensuring commutativity of a ring, due to Jacobson, is the following: for every element r of R there exists an integer [...] such that [...] If, r2 = r for every r, the ring is called <b>Boolean</b> <b>ring.</b> More general conditions which guarantee commutativity of a ring are also known.|$|E
